description: Curated subset of graph expressiveness pairs for diagnostic evaluation demo

hypothesis_scorecard.evidence_summary: Diagonal nRWPE breaks spectral invariance (tanh diag match fraction: 0.0000)
hypothesis_scorecard.key_caveat: The spectral invariance breaking comes from EDMD + off-diagonal structure, not diagonal nonlinearity alone.

hypothesis_scorecard.evidence_summary: KW-PE uses absolute value for sign canonicalization, which is a simple post-processing step. However, EDMD itself introduces eigenvector sign ambiguity similar to LapPE. The sign canonicity test passed with max deviation ~2.1, indicating numerical sensitivity.
hypothesis_scorecard.key_caveat: Sign canonicalization via absolute value may lose information.

hypothesis_scorecard.evidence_summary: Full KW-PE (with EDMD) distinguishes all 64 cospectral pairs tested. Diagonal nRWPE alone is likely spectrally invariant, but the full pipeline succeeds via off-diagonal/trajectory information.
hypothesis_scorecard.key_caveat: Diagonal-only nRWPE may NOT distinguish cospectral graphs.

hypothesis_scorecard.evidence_summary: KW-PE requires EDMD which involves SVD/eigendecomposition of the Koopman matrix. Precompute time: 3.8ms/graph for KW-PE vs 0.12ms/graph for RWPE and LapPE. KW-PE is ~32x slower.
hypothesis_scorecard.key_caveat: EDMD eigendecomposition is the bottleneck; RWPE avoids this entirely.

hypothesis_scorecard.evidence_summary: No KW-PE/nRWPE variant outperforms RWPE on ZINC. RWPE best: 0.1707. Best nonlinear variant: nrwpe_diag at ~0.1825. KW-PE (iter2): 0.3354. Tanh compression likely destroys return-probability information.
hypothesis_scorecard.key_caveat: Expressiveness does not translate to downstream performance for KW-PE/nRWPE.
